The paper proposes a novel approach for motion planning for humanoid robots in complex and dynamically changing environments. This involves finding valid end-poses for the robot while ensuring collision-free configurations. The paper utilizes an online update algorithm to enable efficient reconstruction of the reachability map. This work involves robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG).
